description: Bangladesh's interim government, seeking justice, emphasizes the return of deposed PM Sheikh Hasina and places responsibility on India regarding her extradition. Hasina's diplomatic passport has been cancelled, questioning her stay in India. The chief adviser of the interim government, Muhammad Yunus, will participate in the 79th UNGA session this month.
title: India's call whether to hand over Hasina or not: Bangladesh interim govt
Telangana rain: Mother-daughter duo die in sleep as house collapses

description: Several trainee sub-inspectors arrested by the Special Operations Group for alleged exam misconduct showed poor performance in a retest. Their high scores in the RPSC 2021 exams contrasted sharply with the retest results, raising concerns about the exams' integrity. The incident has highlighted potential flaws in Rajasthan's examination system.
title: Cops' report card: Rajasthan trainee SI 'toppers' fail miserably in retest after arrest
'We want justice': RG Kar protest reaches Ladakh peak

description: Former Trinamool MP Kunal Ghosh has reached out to the RG Kar rape-murder victim's father, pledging party corrective actions based on their feedback. The father emphasized speeding up the slow-paced CBI investigation. Bengal assembly will discuss a bill to make rapes punishable by death, likely in tribute to the victim.
title: 'We may have hurt ...': TMC reaches out to RG Kar victim’s kin, vows party ‘course-correction’

description: ACP Lalit Mohan Negi retired after 35 years in Delhi's special cell, credited with 47 eliminations, including Pakistani terrorists. Renowned for his informer network and resourcefulness, he played a significant role in dismantling the Indian Mujahideen. Post-retirement, Negi intends to focus on improving schools in his hometown while feeling he still has more to accomplish.
title: Meet ACP Lalit Mohan Negi, the mastermind behind city's anti-terror ops
Kerala ADGP is a 'notorious criminal': Left alliance MLA

description: A car accident near Delhi Public School in Ghaziabad resulted in the death of a Delhi Police constable and a daily wager. Two others were critically injured as the speeding vehicle lost control and ran over individuals sleeping on a footpath. Police are now searching for two passengers who fled the scene.
title: Delhi cop, man die after car crash

description: Preethi Pal became the first Indian woman to earn two track and field medals at the Paralympics, securing bronzes in the 100m and 200m T35 categories. Nishad Kumar won a second consecutive silver in the men's high jump T47 category. Rakesh Kumar also advanced in archery at the Games.
title: Paralympics: Preethi makes history, Nishad wins another silver

description: Rajasthan Police's special operations group has apprehended former RPSC member Ramu Ram Raika for reportedly leaking the 2021 sub-inspector recruitment exam paper to his children, who excelled in the test. His daughter Shobha Raika, son Devesh Raika, and three other trainee SIs are in police remand till September 7 for further scrutiny.
title: Exam paper leak: Rajasthan PSC ex-official held for helping his kids 'top' exam
CJI pitches for all-India judicial services to fill vacancies and reduce pendency
Former Hurriyat member joins PDP ahead of J&K elections
Woman saves 6-year-old son from wolf’s jaws in UP's Bahraich

description: Congress's Kerala unit president K Sudhakaran expelled former AICC member Simi Rosebell John after she claimed a 'casting couch' culture within the party. Susan alleged that women had to 'impress' men for positions, sparking complaints from several women functionaries. The party considered her remarks defamatory and expelled her for insulting its women members.
title: Kerala Congress expels AICC ex-member Simi after 'casting couch' allegations
Kharge: Youth will spell BJP's poll defeat as unemployment rate in J&K is 28.2%
K'taka CM Sidda's office spends Rs 54L/month on social media: RTI reply
Minority-run shops in Chamoli attacked after teen 'molested'

description: From 2017 to 2022, there were 1,551 reported cases of rape/gangrape with murder, averaging nearly five cases each week. Uttar Pradesh had the highest number of incidents, followed by Madhya Pradesh and Assam. Despite a 65% conviction rate, the backlog in courts has doubled, with many cases closed due to lack of evidence.
title: 5 rape-murder cases a week reported during '17-'22: Study

description: CBI is investigating financial corruption at RG Kar Medical College and Hospital, focusing on irregularities in the disposal of biomedical waste. Officers uncovered inquiry committee documents implicating hospital workers and two out-of-state biomedical waste recycling firms. The agency is questioning those involved to understand the alleged profitable scheme of diverting biomedical waste.
title: Kolkata rape-murder: CBI lens on biomedical waste scam flagged earlier at RG Kar
2 killed as Manipur rebels open fire, drop explosives from drones
Veteran journalist Umesh Upadhyay dies in freak mishap

description: State Bank of India has released a revamped FASTag design for Vehicle Class 4, which includes cars, jeeps, and vans. This new design aims to improve vehicle identification and toll collection, reducing travel times for commuters. Alongside the FASTag, SBI introduced the MTS RuPay NCMC prepaid card and the OneView mobile application for better payment solutions and account management.
title: SBI launches new FASTag to reduce travel time on highways: Who can use
Railways in a fix over recruitment under merged service regime

description: Sanjay Roy, the primary accused in the RG Kar Medical College rape and murder case, declares his innocence. During a polygraph test, he denied involvement and stated he discovered the victim unconscious. His lawyer points to potential security lapses that could suggest another culprit, raising compelling questions.
title: Kolkata rape-murder: Prime accused tells lawyer he wants to plead 'not guilty'

description: India face a day packed with medal matches at the Paris Paralympics, as the contingent aims to conclude their badminton campaign on a high note. Tokyo gold medallist Sumit Antil will also be in the spotlight as he looks to defend his gold medal in the Javelin Throw F64 event.
title: Paris Paralympics September 2: India's Full Schedule

description: Recent militant attacks in Pakistan's Balochistan and Khyber Pakhtunkhwa provinces have intensified, targeting security forces and civilians. The Baloch Liberation Army conducted significant strikes, demonstrating enhanced combat capabilities with modern weapons. Islamabad's internal security is questioned as both Baloch separatists and Tehreek-i-Taliban Pakistan increase their offenses.
title: Attacks in Balochistan bid to derail SCO summit in October: Pakistan govt
Telangana rains: PM Modi speaks to CMs of Andhra and Telangana; assures Central assistance

description: Two individuals, including a woman, were killed and nine others injured in Manipur's Koutruk and Kadangband areas during an attack by suspected militants. The militants targeted low-lying valley areas, causing heavy damage and panic. Security forces have been deployed to stabilize the situation, and the state government condemned the attack.
title: Manipur violence: 2 killed as militants use drones, bombs in latest attack

description: Simi Rose Bell John, former Congress member, was expelled by the Kerala Pradesh Congress Committee for making derogatory remarks against women leaders. Her allegations of exploitative behavior sparked outrage, leading to a request for action from female party members. A KPCC investigation into the claims is forthcoming.
title: Cong expels woman leader who alleged 'casting couch' exists in Kerala unit

description: The Cellular Operators Association of India has urged the government to impose traceability and user privacy regulations on OTT communication services like WhatsApp and Telegram.
title: Reliance Jio, Airtel, Vodafone to govt: Not regulating WhatsApp, Telegram, Google, others can be 'national security threat'

description: "Engagement is the only way that plays an important role in resolving challenges and expanding relations. Countries and international organizations should engage positively with the Islamic Emirate," Taliban official said.
title: Taliban appeals for 'engagement' after passing draconian morality law

description: Sharad Pawar, president of NCP (SP), declared that the opposition would continue its efforts to unseat the Eknath Shinde government in Maharashtra. This announcement followed the collapse of Shivaji's statue in Sindhudurg, leading to accusations of corruption against the Mahayuti government. A new administration, he asserted, should be founded on Shivaji Maharaj's ideals.
title: 'Maha govt will change ... ': Sharad Pawar attacks ruling alliance over Shivaji statue row

description: Rahul Gandhi accused the BJP government of not addressing rising violence against minorities. Citing incidents in Haryana and Maharashtra, he urged strict actions against attackers. Gandhi emphasized that such violence undermines India's unity and constitutional principles, and reiterated the Congress party's commitment to combating hatred and fostering national unity.
title: 'Mute spectator': Rahul attacks BJP over incidents of mob violence linked to beef

description: In the US Open 2024, Yulia Putintseva faced criticism for an awkward moment with a ball girl in a match against Jasmine Paolini. Putintseva explained her frustration and apologized. Paolini advanced to the fourth round with a 6-3, 6-4 victory and continues her strong performance in the Grand Slams this year.
title: Watch: US Open's 'ugly moment' between player and ball girl

description: Rajasthan education minister Madan Dilawar expressed intentions to burn any books that depict Mughal emperor Akbar as a great figure. He stated that comparing Akbar to Maharana Pratap is disrespectful. A committee will be formed to review textbooks for content that negatively affects the portrayal of national heroes or instills a sense of inferiority in students.
title: Will burn all books glorifying Mughal emperor Akbar: Rajasthan edu min

description: The BJP MLAs and RSS leaders had a six-hour closed-door meeting in New Delhi. The Election Commission announced polls in J&K and Haryana, postponing Maharashtra's elections due to heavy rains and festivals. In the latest Lok Sabha elections, BJP-led Mahayuti struggled in Maharashtra, securing just 17 out of 48 seats against MVA's 30 seats.
title: 'Routine' meet behind closed doors: BJP MLAs from Mumbai confer with RSS leaders

description: Charles Leclerc's bold one-stop strategy led Ferrari to a rare victory at the Formula 1 Italian Grand Prix. Holding off challenges from Oscar Piastri and Lando Norris despite tyre wear, Leclerc's win represented Ferrari's second triumph at its home circuit in 14 races, thrilling passionate home fans.
title: Formula One: Charles Leclerc secures Ferrari victory at Italian Grand Prix, McLaren duo complete podium

description: Shan Masood, the Test captain of Pakistan, faced major backlash on social media after missing a crucial catch in the second Test against Bangladesh in Rawalpindi. His error enabled Liton Das, who was dropped earlier, to score 138. Pakistan ended the day at 9 for 2 in their second innings, leading by 21 runs.
title: 'Na batting, na fielding, na captaincy': Pak captain trolled for...

description: Kangana Ranaut's upcoming film Emergency will not be released on September 6 as planned due to ongoing controversies. The film is still awaiting clearance from the Central Board of Film Certification (CBFC), which has led to the postponement of its release.
title: Kangana Ranaut's Emergency gets postponed, won't release on Sept 6

description: Paytm CEO Vijay Shekhar Sharma compared OpenAI’s ChatGPT to talking Taylor Swift to a grandfather familiar with Bono and Roger Waters, highlighting its data mining limitations. He praised Perplexity AI as perpetually intelligent, referencing recent screenshots showing its advantage over ChatGPT. Perplexity AI launched in August 2022, earlier than ChatGPT, which debuted in November 2022.
title: Paytm CEO: ChatGPT is like talking Taylor Swift to grand father…

description: Israeli soldiers discovered the bodies of six hostages in a Gaza underground tunnel, brutally murdered by Hamas shortly before recovery. With 101 hostages still in Gaza, Prime Minister Netanyahu vowed retaliation. Amid rising violence in the West Bank, public pressure and protests mount in Israel for swift governmental action to secure the hostages' release.
title: Anger grows in Israel after Hamas kills 6 hostages; Netanyahu vows to 'settle score'
11 dead after truck crashes into bar in Dominican Republic

description: More than 100 villages are submerged and 99 trains cancelled due to heavy rains in Telangana. Chief minister A Revanth Reddy held an emergency meeting to assess the situation, with NDRF teams dispatched following central directives. Schools in Hyderabad are closed, and a red warning is issued until Monday morning for several districts.
title: Telangana battles heavy rains: Over 100 villages submerged, 99 trains cancelled

description: In Almora district, Uttarakhand, BJP leader Bhagwat Singh Bora was arrested for allegedly molesting a 14-year-old girl on August 24. The BJP expelled Bora following the incident. The registered case under the POCSO Act underscores the Pushkar Dhami government's 'zero tolerance' stance on crime. The opposition has criticized the BJP government for enabling atrocities against women.
title: Uttarakhand BJP leader held for 'molesting' teen girl, expelled from party

description: President Droupadi Murmu acknowledged the Supreme Court's key role in increasing public trust in the judiciary. Speaking at the National Conference of District Judiciary, she pointed out the ongoing challenge of case backlogs. She urged coordinated action among judiciary, government, and police to address these challenges and highlighted the pressing need for timely justice, particularly for the marginalized.
title: 'Culture of adjournments': Prez Murmu flags major challenges facing the courts

description: Former Australian Test captain Tim Paine, recently appointed as the head coach of the Adelaide Strikers, blended humor and expertise in a social media post highlighting a bowler's misdelivery. Paine's new role follows his stint as an assistant coach and aims to build on the Strikers' promising finish last BBL season.
title: Watch: Spin gone wrong! Ex-Aussie captain's hilarious plea

description: A political division has emerged among military families after Donald Trump's visit to Arlington National Cemetery. Criticized for politicizing a solemn event, Trump defended his actions with supportive family videos. Vice President Kamala Harris condemned Trump, adding to the debate on who should be accountable for the Afghanistan debacle and what defines patriotism.
title: In alarming sign, US military veterans split publicly over support for Donald Trump

description: The ministry of home affairs has created an Inter-Ministerial Central Team to evaluate the flooding damage in Gujarat. Directed by the NIDM executive director, the team will visit affected districts. Gujarat endured severe rainfall between August 25 to 30, causing 47 fatalities. More heavy rainfall is anticipated until September 5, according to the IMD.
title: MHA deploys inter-ministerial team to assess Gujarat flood damage

description: The Federation of All India Medical Association (FAIMA) has requested the Indian Medical Association (IMA) to reconsider Ketan Desai's role as chief patron amid concerns about electoral integrity and alleged corruption. Desai, previously arrested in 2010 for accepting a bribe, was elected president of World Medical Association in 2016 after all charges were withdrawn.
title: 'Reconsider role of Ketan Desai as IMA chief patron': FAIMA urges doctors' body

description: August's GST collections reached Rs 1,74,962 crore, registering a 10% year-on-year growth.  Compared month-over-month, there was a decline from Rs 182,075 crore in July. April saw the highest GST collection of Rs 2.10 lakh crore.
title: GST collections rise 10% to Rs 1.75 lakh cr in August

description: Pro-Khalistan radical groups in Canada held parades commemorating the 1995 assassination of Punjab Chief Minister Beant Singh. The floats depicted the assassination scene, celebrating the killer. The events were condemned by Canada's Minister of Public Safety. Similar rallies in Toronto were led by Inderjeet Singh Gosal. Canada’s Minister of Public Safety condemned the incidents.
title: Pro-Khalistan groups in Canada honour Beant Singh's assassin with floats

description: In Vadodara, two volunteers from the Gujarat Society for Prevention of Cruelty to Animals were seen transporting a rescued crocodile on a two-wheeler. The reptile, rescued from a sub-station, was taken to the forest department to avoid potential harm from a gathering crowd, leading to a viral video that has amused many in the city.
title: Watch: Crocodile out for a ride on a two-wheeler!

description: Bayley, a prominent WWE star and Damage CTRL leader, keeps her personal life private. She ended a decade-long relationship with Aaron Solow in 2021 due to differing visions for their future. She cleared rumors of romantic links with Finn Balor and Seth Collins, emphasizing her single status. Fans hope for her future happiness.
title: Who is ex-boyfriend of Bayley? Personal life of former WWE women's champion

description: Nicholas Pooran, playing for Trinbago Knight Riders, set a new world record for the most sixes in a calendar year in T20 cricket during a Caribbean Premier League match. He hit nine sixes in his 43-ball 97, surpassing Chris Gayle's previous record of 135 sixes in 2015. Pooran's impressive form has seen him hit 139 sixes in 2024.
title: Nicholas Pooran breaks Chris Gayle's massive T20 world record

description: Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar expressed concern over the rape and murder of a trainee doctor at Kolkata's RG Kar Medical College, criticising comments by senior advocate Kapil Sibal and NGO silence on the incident. He called for public sensitivity and stronger measures to ensure women's safety amid the national outrage.
title: VP Dhankhar slams 'stray voices and silent NGOs' over Kolkata horror

description: The Aam Aadmi Party accused BJP of kidnapping councillor Ram Chander ahead of MCD elections. Chander, who briefly defected to BJP and then rejoined AAP, claimed BJP threatened him with legal action. BJP denied these allegations, stating Chander was at home. The incident has intensified pre-election tensions.
title: Aam Aadmi Party cries councillor 'kidnapped'; BJP rubbishes claim

description: In a light-hearted event, Australian cricketers like Pat Cummins and Mitchell Marsh took lie-detector tests on the Fox League YouTube channel, facing amusing questions. The team is on a white-ball tour of the United Kingdom, followed by a home summer that includes a series of T20Is and ODIs against Pakistan and a five-match Test series against India.
title: Watch: Australian cricketers' hilarious lie-detector test

description: A nurse was allegedly molested by a patient at a government hospital in West Bengal's Birbhum district while giving a saline drip. The patient, brought in with a high fever, has been arrested, and an investigation is ongoing. According to the nurse's complaint, the patient not only touched her inappropriately but also used offensive language during the encounter. This incident underscores a troubling rise in violence against healthcare workers, particularly in West Bengal.
title: Patient held for 'molesting' nurse at govt hospital in Birbhum

description: A 13-year-old girl receiving pneumonia treatment was allegedly molested by a laboratory technician in the CT scan room at a Howrah hospital. After disclosing the assault to her mother, the technician was confronted and arrested. The hospital administration and police are investigating, providing security to the victim and family during the ongoing probe. A video of the confrontation between the girl's mother and the accused has circulated on social media.
title: Lab technician 'molests' 13-yr-old girl in Howrah hospital, arrested

description: Tejashwi Yadav from Rashtriya Janata Dal provoked JDU to support adding reservations in the Ninth Schedule during state-wide protests for a caste census. He accused the BJP ally of disregarding Bihar's demands for special status. The BJP retorted, criticizing RJD for not securing reservations in Panchayats while in power.
title: 'We challenge JDU to ... ': What Tejashwi Yadav said during RJD's protest for caste census

description: Palestinian health authorities and UN agencies have initiated an extensive polio vaccination campaign in Gaza, aiming to vaccinate about 640,000 children. The drive faces significant challenges due to ongoing conflict, destruction, and displacement. The initiative underscores the urgent need for a temporary truce to allow families to safely access health facilities.
title: Massive polio vaccination campaign launched in war-torn Gaza

description: Jonty Rhodes, fielding coach for Lucknow Super Giants, applauded KL Rahul's leadership abilities since 2022, marked by consistent playoff appearances. Although LSG faced a challenging 2024 season, Rhodes highlighted Rahul's role in creating a competitive culture. Positive discussions between team owner Sanjiv Goenka and Rahul hint at his retention for future seasons.
title: IPL: Rhodes praises KL Rahul amid speculation over future with LSG

description: Mammootty urges the Malayalam film industry to stand united in implementing the Hema Committee’s recommendations for addressing sexual harassment. He dismisses the notion of a 'power center' and advocates for honest police investigations. His comments follow Mohanlal's remarks on the industry's crisis, highlighting the need for collective action among film associations.
title: 'Ultimately the movie must survive': Mammootty rejects 'power center' in Mollywood

description: Residents of Vadodara in Gujarat displayed their unwavering love for Garba by dancing in knee-deep water despite flooded streets during Janmashtami. The viral video has gained attention online. The IMD has warned about upcoming heavy rains from a new weather system, adding to the region's challenges, but traditional celebrations continue.
title: Watch: Gujarat residents perform Garba in flooded streets

description: Rahul Gandhi participated in a virtual meeting with senior Congress leaders to focus relief efforts in Wayanad after devastating landslides. He highlighted the necessity of revitalizing tourism and correcting misconceptions about safety. Gandhi emphasized the need for inter-departmental coordination, adequate compensation, and resolving livelihood issues to assist the area’s recovery.
title: 'Revitalise tourism': Rahul holds meet with Cong leaders on Wayanad

description: The sea walnut, a species of comb jelly native to the eastern Atlantic Ocean, can reverse its ageing process by reverting to a larval stage when conditions are harsh. This ability is thought to boost its invasive success. Findings from a bioRxiv preprint suggest that this phenomenon could provide insights into ageing processes.
title: Sea Walnut's can age in reverse: Breakthrough discovery in comb jellies

description: Jeffrey Piccolo filed a lawsuit against Disney after his wife died from an allergic reaction at a Disney World restaurant. Disney initially claimed his Disney+ subscription barred court proceedings but later decided to let the case proceed in court. The decision follows public backlash and aims for a sensitive resolution.
title: Disney+ membership also has a 'death clause,' finds a dead woman's family

description: Joe Root's consecutive centuries in the second Test against Sri Lanka too him past Alastair Cook's record for most Test hundreds by an England batsman. Root now stands at 12377 Test runs, approaching Sachin Tendulkar's 15921. Root underlines the joy of personal milestones but remains focused on team victories. England's upcoming schedule includes six more Tests this year.
title: 3544 runs behind, will Root break Tendulkar's record?

description: The Maha Vikas Aghadi (MVA) held a protest march in Mumbai following the collapse of the Chhatrapati Shivaji Maharaj statue in Sindhudurg district. Notable leaders such as Sharad Pawar and Uddhav Thackeray attended. The demonstration, called 'jode maro,' was directed at the Mahayuti government, resulting in heightened police security in the city.
title: Shivaji statue collapse: MVA leaders lead 'jode maro' protest in Mumbai

description: President Joe Biden expressed devastation over the recovery of six hostages' bodies, including an Israeli-American, from Gaza. He condemned Hamas and vowed to secure remaining hostages. Israeli forces retrieved the bodies, including American Hersh Goldberg-Polin. Vice President Kamala Harris and Israeli President Isaac Herzog also condemned Hamas's actions, calling for an end to the conflict.
title: 'Hamas will pay': US Prez Biden after American hostage's found in Gaza

description: At WWE's Bash in Berlin on August 31, 2024, Cody Rhodes retained the Undisputed WWE Championship against Kevin Owens, and Gunther defended his title against Randy Orton. Bianca Belair and Jade Cargill reclaimed the Women's Tag Team Championship. The event featured five matches, including a Strap Match and a mixed tag team bout.
title: WWE bash in Berlin 2024: Full results, winners & must-see highlights

description: KC Tyagi has stepped down as the national spokesperson for Janata Dal (United), citing personal reasons. Rajiv Prasad Ranjan is named his successor. Tyagi, in a letter to Party chief Nitish Kumar, expressed his inability to continue due to other commitments but pledged to support the party and Bihar government's achievements.
title: KC Tyagi quits as JD(U) spokesperson; replaced by Rajiv Ranjan Prasad

description: A Delta Airlines passenger was ejected from a flight for wearing a controversial shirt featuring Donald Trump flipping the bird and referencing a viral video. Despite initially complying with a request to turn the shirt inside-out after a complaint, the passenger reverted it back to its original position, leading to his removal just before takeoff.
title: 'Hawk tuah on...': Man kicked out of Delta flight over Trump t-shirt

description: Pakistan's Salman Ali Agha defended captain Babar Azam after another disappointing batting performance in the second Test against Bangladesh. Babar, struggling for form, was dismissed for 31 runs, contributing to Pakistan's batting collapse. Salman remains confident that Babar, despite his recent poor form, will soon return to scoring big runs for Pakistan.
title: 'There are 10 other players in the team': Teammate defends Babar Azam

description: A handwritten note with the word 'Blast' was found on toilet paper in an Indigo Airlines flight from Jabalpur to Hyderabad, prompting an emergency landing in Nagpur. The aircraft, carrying 69 passengers and four crew members, was diverted, and all passengers were evacuated safely. Emergency services were mobilised for further investigations.Jabalpur-Hyderabad IndiGo Flight Makes Emergency Landing at Nagpur Airport After Bomb Threat Note Found in Toilet
title: Bomb threat: IndiGo flight makes emergency landing in Nagpur

description: Uber is returning its premium Uber Black service to India after nearly a decade. Initially launching in select Mumbai areas, the service will use larger vehicles like SUVs and MUVs and will cost 30-40% more than Uber Premier.
title: Uber Black to return to India after 10 years, with this likely change

description: Officials in Uttar Pradesh's Bahraich district have ramped up 'Operation Bhediya' to capture wolves accountable for eight deaths over two months. Four wolves have been caught, with efforts continuing to find two more. Drones and traps are employed for safe capture, while precautions ensure residents' safety amidst the ongoing investigation.
title: 'Operation Bhediya' intensifies with 4 wolves captured, 2 more sought

description: Hyderabad faces devastating floods as torrential rain caused by a Bay of Bengal depression impacts several districts. Khammam district experiences 52 cm of rainfall. Other districts including Warangal and Mahabubabad see over 40 cm of rain. IMD predicts heavy rain in many other districts, potentially leading to more floods.
title: Torrential rains unleash chaos in Telangana

description: Gautam Gambhir's early days as India's head coach began with mixed outcomes; India clinched the T20 series 3-0 against Sri Lanka but faced a 2-0 defeat in the ODIs. Jonty Rhodes supports Gambhir's drive for excellence, predicting better team synchronization soon. India's next challenge under Gambhir is a two-Test series against Bangladesh later this month.
title: 'Gambhir just wants...' - Jonty's views on Team India coach

description: At the US Open, Beatriz Haddad Maia's victory over Anna Kalinskaya was marred by a contentious video review decision. The incident spotlighted the ongoing debate about the need for consistent use of video technology in tennis. Expanded this year to more courts, the review system faces scrutiny and calls for refinement following several high-profile controversies.
title: US Open controversy: Beatriz advances after a video review row

description: Elon Musk's favored interview question is 'Tell me about some of the most difficult problems you worked on and how you solved them.' Rooted in psychological principles, this technique helps identify dishonesty while seeking candidates with a proven track record in problem-solving and innovation.
title: Musk’s favourite 'time-tested' job interview question, says can be a good 'lie-detector' test

description: Elon Musk is concerned that his social media platform, X, could face challenges in the US if Kamala Harris and Tim Walz gain power. He points to recent issues in Brazil, where a Supreme Court order banned X. Musk believes such actions are unprecedented attacks on free speech in the 21st century. He also raised concerns about Harris and Walz speeches.
title: What will happen to free speech in America if Kamala/Waltz gains power? Elon Musk answers

description: The Israeli military has identified the bodies of six hostages, including Israeli-American Hersh Goldberg-Polin, recovered from a Gaza tunnel. The hostages were killed by Hamas militants shortly before an Israeli rescue attempt. The discovery has intensified calls for negotiations to secure the release of the remaining hostages.
title: Bodies of six hostages found in Gaza tunnel

description: Samit Dravid, son of Rahul Dravid, has been picked for the India under-19 team for an upcoming series against Australia U-19. He has gained attention for his impressive performances in age-group cricket, particularly as a batsman with strong technical skills, while his father emphasizes letting him develop at his own pace.
title: Watch: Samit Dravid's reaction on selection in under-19 squad

description: Joe Root has reached a historic milestone by scoring his 34th Test century during the second Test against Sri Lanka at Lord's. This achievement makes him the highest century-maker for England in Test cricket. Root also became the first England cricketer to score 50 international centuries and broke several other records, including the most runs scored at Lord's.
title: Joe Root breaks multiple records with twin Test centuries at Lord's

description: Nine people lost their lives as heavy rains wreaked havoc in Andhra Pradesh, particularly in Krishna and Guntur districts, disrupting daily life and affecting power, road, and rail transport. The torrential downpour triggered landslides, floods, and infrastructure damage, leading authorities to announce school holidays and advise residents to stay indoors unless necessary.
title: 9 killed as record rain lashes Andhra, floods roads & triggers landslide

description: Former President Donald Trump advocates decriminalizing small marijuana amounts, arguing that arrests waste taxpayer dollars. Citing Florida’s Amendment 3, he noted it aims to legalize up to 3 ounces for adults. Trump calls for laws banning public use and addresses the dangers of fentanyl-laced marijuana.
title: What is Donald Trump's take on possessing small amounts of marijuana?

description: Olympic wrestler Vinesh Phogat joined farmers at the Shambhu and Khanauri borders in Punjab and Haryana, supporting their 200-day protest for minimum support price. She urged the government to heed farmers' demands, stressing their crucial role. Farmers plan further protests around the Lakhimpur Kheri incident anniversary.
title: 'Listen to those who feed the country': Vinesh Phogat to govt

description: A second landslide struck Varunavat Parvat in Uttarkashi, causing the evacuation of 32 families. The incident has stirred memories of similar landslides in 2003. An expert team will soon assess the situation. Additionally, debris from a landslide in Chamoli’s Pagnau village entered homes, prompting authorities to relocate villagers.
title: Uttarakhand: 2nd round of landslides, 32 families asked to evacuate

description: Despite his casual persona and reputation for forgetfulness, Indian cricket captain Rohit Sharma is recognised as an intelligent player with sharp game awareness. Umpire Anil Chaudhary commends Rohit Sharma's exceptional batting skills, praising his footwork, ball sense, and ability to handle tough deliveries, indicating a deep understanding of cricket. Chaudhary asserts that while Rohit may appear casual, he actually possesses a sharp and intelligent cricketing mind.
title: 'Rohit Sharma sirf lagta casual hai, hai nahi'

description: Nine-year-old Shreyovi Mehta from Faridabad, India, has earned runner-up in the '10 Years and Under' category of the Wildlife Photographer of the Year award. Her photo "In the Spotlight," featuring peahens in Keoladev National Park, was selected from nearly 60,000 entries. She will receive a medal at the award ceremony in London in October.
title: 9-yr old Indian runner-up in London wildlife photography contest

description: A man, Shahzad alias Saifi, was arrested for attempting to breach security and attack Union minister Giriraj Singh at a 'Janta Darbaar' event in Bihar's Begusarai. The police intervened and detained Saifi. Singh condemned the attack, emphasizing ongoing communal tension and his resolve to continue his work despite such incidents.
title: Watch: Man attempts to punch Union min Giriraj over hate speech

description: San Francisco 49ers' wide receiver Ricky Pearsall was shot during an attempted robbery in downtown San Francisco. The 23-year-old is in serious but stable condition. The incident took place in the Union Square area, where both Pearsall and the suspect were hurt and transported to a hospital. The suspect is currently in custody.
title: San Francisco 49ers' Ricky Pearsall shot in robbery attempt

description: Apple and IBM both announced layoffs this week, with Apple revealing its iPhone 16 event date. Telegram’s CEO faced charges for misuse of the app. Vivo and Realme launched new smartphones in India. The RBI introduced a UPI cash deposit feature, and Reliance Jio unveiled JioTvOS, JioHome, and JioTV+.
title: Apple iPhone 16 launch dates announced and other top tech news of the week

description: Gujarat is expected to face heavy rainfall again starting Sunday, due to a depression moving from the Bay of Bengal towards the state and Maharashtra. The heavy rains from Aug 25 to Aug 29 resulted in 47 deaths across various districts. More rain is anticipated in Saurashtra, central, and south Gujarat regions until Sept 5.
title: Gujarat braces for another spell of heavy rain, death toll at 47

description: Five men and two teens have been detained in Haryana for allegedly lynching Sabir Malik, a 24-year-old migrant worker from Bengal, suspected of consuming beef. The incident has sparked political criticism regarding law enforcement. Malik's body has been returned to his West Bengal family, while migrant workers in the village fear for their safety.
title: Bengal labourer lynched in Haryana on suspicion of eating beef

description: IndiGo's Mumbai airport operations have been severely impacted by a turf war between two unions, Bharatiya Kamgar Sena (BKS) and Hawai Karmachari Sena (Hakse), over wheelchair job allocations. Frequent flash strikes and reassignments have delayed baggage handling and flights, affecting thousands of passengers. The conflict centers on IndiGo's ground-handling subsidiary, Agile Airports Services, ongoing since July.
title: Battle for wheelchair duty tips hits baggage handling, delays Mumbai flights

description: Mahendra Singh Dhoni and Virat Kohli, legendary figures in Indian cricket, share a deep mutual respect. Their bond has been crucial to Indian cricket's success. Dhoni transitioned to a mentor role and supported Kohli's career profoundly. Their friendship, characterized by guidance and camaraderie, continues robustly even after Dhoni's international retirement.
title: 'I don't know whether...': Dhoni on his relationship with Virat - Watch
